{"key":"processedPost-10985047","value":{"id":10985047,"first":10984721,"last":10985336,"when":1251901204,"utime":"09/02/09 05:20 PM","content":"If you want to soak substrate trays, simply place them in a clean sink with the drain open.&nbsp; Allow the faucet to slowly run until it fills the tray and begins to run over.&nbsp; Let it slowly overflow for an hour or two and then dump out any water that hasn't absorbed.&nbsp; Cakes soak for 12 to 24 hours, but that's too long for bulk substrates.<br />I've tried the tubing idea several times and every single time it caused green molds.&nbsp; The molds travel through the tubing when there's not water in it and then they get to the center of the substrate where they wreck havoc.<br />RR","title":"Re: Dunking 2lb bread trays full of hpoo"}}